question.en:
An algorithm processes n items by dividing the problem in half each iteration until reaching base cases of size 1. What is its time complexity in Big O notation?
python
def process(arr):
    if len(arr) <= 1:
        return arr
    mid = len(arr) // 2
    left = process(arr[:mid])
    right = process(arr[mid:])
    return merge(left, right)

