question.en:
Consider a binary search tree (BST) where you need to find the lowest common ancestor (LCA) of two nodes. Which statement about tree traversal is correct?
java
// LCA: lowest common ancestor
Node lca(Node root, int p, int q) {
    if (root == null) return null;
    if (root.val > Math.max(p, q)) return lca(root.left, p, q);
    if (root.val < Math.min(p, q)) return lca(root.right, p, q);
    return root;
}

